{
  "text": "Above theoretical observations have been verified with 3D numerical homogenization (see e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . For our experiments we have used a 3D numerical homogenization code very similar to the 2D homogenization code provided by Andreassen and Andreasen (2014), but utilizing the parallel solvers available in PETSc [CITATION_3] . We consider a cubic unit cell and a closed-walled box microstructure with wall-thickness given by one element size. Then we consider the same unit cell but with the material confined to square cross-section frame elements at the 12 edges of the cube as illustrated in Figure 11 .",
  "correct_citation": {
